1
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:12,387
You can tell the dead by the look

2
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:13,847
in their eyes.

3
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:25,358
That woman…

4
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:29,237
was definitely dead.

5
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,989
No, we didn't!

6
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:36,453
I swear we didn't even touch her.
She just died on her own.

7
00:00:37,662 --> 00:00:39,789
Chae-ni! Chae…

8
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:41,875
Chae-ni?

9
00:00:42,959 --> 00:00:44,377
Chae-ni, where did she go?

10
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:46,171
- Mr. Son!
- She was right here.

11
00:00:46,254 --> 00:00:47,130
But then,

12
00:00:48,089 --> 00:00:49,215
she vanished.

13
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,980
What a load of nonsense. Jeju Island?

14
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:05,273
That's what I'm seeing.

15
00:01:09,986 --> 00:01:11,821
Yeah, it's definitely showing Jeju.

16
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:13,823
Maybe Chae-ni's phone is glitchy.

17
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,658
You're the one who's glitchy.

18
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:19,204
Don't you know she hasn't once
left Haeseong since she was seven?

19
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:21,456
Yeah, I know. She's the ghost of Haeseong.

20
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:22,999
But that's what I'm seeing.

21
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,793
Maybe she really is in Jeju.

22
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:40,141
That silly bear isn't here either.

23
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:49,526
She packed her things?

24
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,117
SAVINGS ACCOUNT BANKBOOK

25
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:01,079
DEAREST GRANDMOTHER

26
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:10,004
Yes, this is Kim Jeon-bok.

27
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:13,258
I guess it really was glitchy.
It seems to have been an error.

28
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:15,468
I tried again, and she's in Haeseong.

29
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:17,178
In the Haedeul-ri area.

30
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:28,273
And the victim was Ms. Eun Chae-ni,
the granddaughter of Hearty House?

31
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:29,774
Yes.

32
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,651
I believe so.

33
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,405
Are you talking about that woman
over there?

34
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:39,868
Yes, that's right.

35
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:55,383
Isn't that Chae-ni?

36
00:04:06,537 --> 00:04:10,166
THE WONDERFOOLS

37
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:16,047
EPISODE 2
SECRETS ARE MEANT TO BE KEPT

38
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:21,594
You reported the disposal
of a dead body, correct?

39
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,810
Deny it, okay?

40
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:32,188
Deny it, no matter what.
Deny your butt off.

41
00:04:32,897 --> 00:04:34,774
- That's our only way out.
- Okay.

42
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:41,030
What dead body? Didn't you see earlier
that Eun Chae-ni is fine?

43
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:43,908
We were staking the place out
and took a tumble, okay?

44
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,371
Check this stink out for yourself!

45
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:50,248
I've filed countless complaints,

46
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:53,835
but the only answer I ever get is,
"No, we can't. There's nothing we can do."

47
00:04:53,918 --> 00:04:56,212
You might as well just play a recording.

48
00:05:00,883 --> 00:05:01,926
What else could we do?

49
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:05,930
Since the authorities wouldn't step up,
we had to catch the dumper ourselves.

50
00:05:07,932 --> 00:05:08,808
What shall we do?

51
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,568
I guess I was mistaken.

52
00:05:20,361 --> 00:05:22,155
Then we'll log this as a false alarm.

53
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:25,074
Yes. Please do that.

54
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:29,370
Okay, you can go.

55
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:31,289
We were going to. Let's go.

56
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:33,916
Hey, why would you…

57
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:47,722
What did I tell you?

58
00:05:47,805 --> 00:05:49,557
I said flat-out denial would work.

59
00:05:50,058 --> 00:05:51,684
You can't call it flat-out denial.

60
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:53,895
I used sound logic to persuade them.

61
00:05:53,978 --> 00:05:56,022
That's the difference between me and you.

62
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:58,983
An educated person, an uneducated person.

63
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,402
A good person, a no-good person.

64
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:05,323
A person whose family is filthy rich,
a person who is dirt poor.

65
00:06:06,157 --> 00:06:07,158
Damn it.

66
00:06:08,242 --> 00:06:10,328
Hey, but are you really okay?

67
00:06:10,828 --> 00:06:13,831
I totally thought you were dead.
Why weren't you breathing?

68
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:16,084
I thought I was dead too.

69
00:06:17,085 --> 00:06:18,795
I even saw some weird stuff.

70
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:20,213
What ye doin' o'er there?

71
00:06:21,297 --> 00:06:23,508
Don't loaf around and get outta there.

72
00:06:23,591 --> 00:06:26,761
She kept saying things
that I couldn't understand.

73
00:06:26,844 --> 00:06:30,223
Ain't ye hearin' me?
I said scoot on outta there!

74
00:06:30,306 --> 00:06:33,935
The wind's kickin' up real bad.
At this rate, you ain't gettin' out alone.

75
00:06:34,018 --> 00:06:37,021
Can't ye hear me?
I'm tellin' ya, it's mighty dicey!

76
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:39,690
What ye doin'? Get outta there already!

77
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:43,277
Maybe you had a near-death experience.

78
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:45,113
You know, not actually dying,

79
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:48,199
but just dipping your toes
into the afterlife.

80
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:51,869
Maybe you saw a grim reaper!

81
00:06:51,953 --> 00:06:53,287
You think so?

82
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:56,541
So was I dead or not?

83
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:58,793
Maybe I half-died.

84
00:07:00,044 --> 00:07:02,130
Like a half-dried squid or something?

85
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:05,383
Does your grandma know
the shape you're in?

86
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:07,927
Of course she doesn't.

87
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:09,804
If she did, she'd lose it.

88
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:11,597
Don't you know what she's like?

89
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:14,225
The big cheese of Myeong-dong,
King Jeon-bok.

90
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:16,602
If she finds out…

91
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:17,854
If she finds out?

92
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:19,355
EUN CHAE-NI'S

93
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,690
KIDNAPPERS

94
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:28,197
We're truly sorry, ma'am.

95
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:32,827
Go on and bury them.

96
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:34,287
Yes, ma'am!

97
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:36,456
Please don't do that!

98
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:40,710
Hold it!

99
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:44,464
Why are you over there, not here with us?

100
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:49,135
What was that word
I told you to memorize again?

101
00:07:49,218 --> 00:07:52,054
How diplomats
get away with crimes overseas.

102
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:55,099
- Immunity.
- That's it. Granddaughter immunity.

103
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,269
Is there no
granddaughter's friend immunity?

104
00:07:58,352 --> 00:07:59,395
What do I do now?

105
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,439
Hey, Mr. Son, what should we do?

106
00:08:01,522 --> 00:08:04,525
Why did you rope us into this?
You could've just stolen the money.

107
00:08:04,609 --> 00:08:07,236
It's okay.
We'll make sure we don't get caught.

108
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,654
Flat-out denial always works.

109
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,781
You think denial will cut it?

110
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:12,450
Is that the best you can do?

111
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,368
Who said you'll just deny it?

112
00:08:15,536 --> 00:08:17,622
Deny with passion, with all you've got.

113
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:22,919
Would that actually work?
Then we'd be in the clear, right?

114
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:25,463
Of course. Nothing beats flat-out denial.

115
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:30,468
Did you really

116
00:08:30,551 --> 00:08:34,055
think this plan through carefully?

117
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:36,432
How would you have gotten the 50 million?

118
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,017
Wired to my account, of course.

119
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:40,394
Borrowed accounts are illegal, you know.

120
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:48,528
I had no clue because I'd never
talked to you long enough.

121
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:52,740
That you were a girl
with such an empty head.

122
00:08:52,823 --> 00:08:55,076
To think I trusted bozos like you

123
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:58,788
and co-conspired to get 50 million won…

124
00:08:58,871 --> 00:09:00,331
- Want some?
- What are they?

125
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:03,709
- These are good.
- Right?

126
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,461
Hey, I'm talking to you!

127
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:18,307
This is my fault. It's all my fault.

128
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:22,728
I, a Homo sapiens who conspired
with Neanderthals, am to blame.

129
00:09:24,021 --> 00:09:24,855
If I ever

130
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:28,985
get involved in another ridiculous
fake kidnapping of Eun Chae-ni

131
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:31,988
or another half-dried squid
near-death experience,

132
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:33,823
you can consider me…

133
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:34,865
Screwed.

134
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:42,707
She heard.

135
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,125
Everything.

136
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:02,059
Run!

137
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:18,242
You know the crimes you are guilty of!

138
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:23,164
Punish him mercilessly!

139
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:33,215
I am innocent. Treason, of all crimes?

140
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,676
This is preposterous.

141
00:10:36,385 --> 00:10:38,387
I truly am innocent.

142
00:10:39,055 --> 00:10:43,768
I swear to the heavens above
that I have not one speck of shame.

143
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:44,977
How dare you!

144
00:10:45,936 --> 00:10:49,690
Twist his legs until he confesses!

145
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:57,031
I have done no wrong!

146
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:12,713
Is this thing really glitching?

147
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:16,676
Come out.

148
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:21,055
Come here
before I get people to drag you out!

149
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:28,479
Ms. Kim…

150
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:32,024
Could you please move…

151
00:11:35,528 --> 00:11:37,321
That… No, it's okay.

152
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,739
Thank you.

153
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:44,245
Just moving one of your legs
is more than enough for me to get out.

154
00:11:44,328 --> 00:11:45,413
Like this.

155
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:57,717
- You must be furious.
- I tried to talk her out of it.

156
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:01,053
- But it was all Chae-ni's plan.
- I said, "Think about your grandma."

157
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:03,889
- She said we'd get five million each--
- I really tried--

158
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:08,811
In other words, the three of you

159
00:12:09,645 --> 00:12:12,106
staged a kidnapping for money?

160
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:16,694
- I wouldn't quite put it like that.
- Mr. Son here wouldn't fix my roof.

161
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:19,321
- Chae-ni planned all of this--
- I just wanted my roof--

162
00:12:21,741 --> 00:12:23,159
Where's your mastermind, Eunie?

163
00:12:23,242 --> 00:12:26,829
That's exactly it!
Eun Chae-ni is the mastermind, Ms. Kim.

164
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:30,875
Eunie.

165
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:35,379
Your accomplices have already betrayed you
without hesitation. Get out here.

166
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:42,762
Why, you always make
things worse for yourself!

167
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:44,555
Get out here!

168
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:49,059
What?

169
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:52,855
I definitely saw her climb in here.

170
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,486
Where were you hiding?

171
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:00,279
Grandma.

172
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:03,240
Can you see me?

173
00:13:03,324 --> 00:13:05,826
What newfangled nonsense is this?

174
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:08,454
Did you think I wouldn't be able
to see you? Get out now!

175
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:11,290
Deary me.

176
00:13:11,373 --> 00:13:12,792
What do I do, Grandma?

177
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:16,420
Something must be really wrong with me.

178
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:20,299
I keep seeing things. What do I do?

179
00:13:20,382 --> 00:13:21,425
How?

180
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:25,137
What feels wrong? How?
Should I call the hospital director?

181
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:27,556
- I don't know.
- Are you running a fever?

182
00:13:28,098 --> 00:13:29,141
- Oh dear.
- I just…

183
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:34,605
Would you look at that?
She's using her granddaughter immunity.

184
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:37,858
Tell me what happened.

185
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:40,653
- Just now, I was in some weird…
- Yes, what is it?

186
00:13:40,736 --> 00:13:42,863
- Yes?
- Grandma!

187
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:45,407
Breathe. Just breathe. And sit down.

188
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:48,452
Sit right here and take a deep breath.

189
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:50,746
Just take a breath.

190
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:53,666
He's annoying.

191
00:13:53,749 --> 00:13:55,876
He's annoying? That's no good.

192
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,628
Hey, you're annoying her!

193
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,258
You're looking for someone?

194
00:14:03,551 --> 00:14:04,426
Who?

195
00:14:05,052 --> 00:14:06,512
The Child of Eternity?

196
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:09,974
I don't know.

197
00:14:11,809 --> 00:14:15,938
There were some children
who survived the fire back then.

198
00:14:17,857 --> 00:14:21,402
But I'm not sure about
this Child of Eternity you speak of.

199
00:14:24,905 --> 00:14:31,078
Oh, but I do remember
one other child very clearly.

200
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:33,789
Number 3972.

201
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:37,543
Because I saved him

202
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,713
from the fire that day.

203
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:49,096
Sir!

204
00:14:49,179 --> 00:14:51,140
Please open this door!

205
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,517
Please open this door!

206
00:14:58,063 --> 00:14:59,398
Number 3972?

207
00:14:59,481 --> 00:15:01,775
You saved that child?

208
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:04,737
Yes, I sure did.

209
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:08,157
And that child

210
00:15:09,366 --> 00:15:11,285
has returned to Haeseong.

211
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:15,497
He's grown into a fine young man.

212
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:18,042
He didn't seem to recognize me,

213
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:21,378
but I recognized him right away.

214
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:23,380
Number 3972.

215
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:26,717
I'm certain it's him.

216
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:29,219
I see.

217
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,430
Thank you for telling me.

218
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:34,099
Here, eat up before it gets cold.

219
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:59,208
I don't know how many years it's been

220
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:01,585
since I sat across from you like this…

221
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:05,631
and ate a hot meal.

222
00:16:11,261 --> 00:16:13,055
After you died,

223
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:17,643
I was sure a day like this
would never come again.

224
00:16:20,604 --> 00:16:23,482
I'm so glad you're here.

225
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:38,998
Did you hear that? Number 3972.

226
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:46,088
Honey.

227
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:50,175
Honey!

228
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:53,887
Where… where am I?

229
00:16:54,638 --> 00:16:55,639
Honey?

230
00:17:04,898 --> 00:17:06,150
NUMBER 3972
ABILITY: TELEKINESIS

231
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,943
What is all this?

232
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:21,183
Don't you have a family?

233
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:24,603
I don't know.

234
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,481
I can't remember.

235
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:29,775
Not even your mom's face?

236
00:18:30,442 --> 00:18:31,485
Or your dad's?

237
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:36,967
Don't worry.

238
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:38,760
I can't die.

239
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:41,680
You can't die?

240
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:55,235
Focus and try again. You can do it.

241
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:40,906
How did he do that?

242
00:20:42,157 --> 00:20:43,659
That's awesome.

243
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:08,976
Stop!

244
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:43,927
You're still doing this, City Hall guy?

245
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:46,305
I asked you
to please keep it down at night!

246
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,515
You're really trying my patience.

247
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:50,934
Knock it off or move out already!

248
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:55,772
I can't die.

249
00:21:59,276 --> 00:22:00,819
But that kid was definitely

250
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:02,988
a boy.

251
00:22:52,913 --> 00:22:53,830
What…

252
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:55,832
Huh?

253
00:22:57,584 --> 00:22:58,502
How?

254
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:02,464
Why, what is it?

255
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:04,883
Is something wrong? Is it very serious?

256
00:23:04,966 --> 00:23:06,426
Well, it's…

257
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:11,139
I'm ready for anything, so just tell me.

258
00:23:11,223 --> 00:23:12,307
Spit it out!

259
00:23:13,517 --> 00:23:14,726
Well,

260
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:16,144
it's very…

261
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:20,857
I don't quite understand
how this has happened either,

262
00:23:20,941 --> 00:23:22,734
but the test results are…

263
00:23:22,818 --> 00:23:24,444
Everything here

264
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:26,822
looks normal.

265
00:23:27,989 --> 00:23:28,824
Come again?

266
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:32,119
If you look at the graphs here,

267
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:35,539
you can see they're all very stable
with no major fluctuations.

268
00:23:35,622 --> 00:23:37,290
This is from last time. This is now.

269
00:23:37,916 --> 00:23:40,252
I checked the ultrasound results, too,

270
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:42,045
and her kidneys look clean.

271
00:23:42,129 --> 00:23:45,132
Even the valvular inflammation
I saw last time is completely gone.

272
00:23:45,215 --> 00:23:49,010
And this is the X-ray we just took.
That one's from last time.

273
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:50,929
Her lungs have cleared up too.

274
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:52,889
Last time, her heart was this big,

275
00:23:53,473 --> 00:23:54,516
but now,

276
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,727
it's back to a completely normal size.

277
00:23:57,811 --> 00:23:59,271
So, you're saying…

278
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,942
To get this straight,

279
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:06,695
you seem to be saying

280
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:08,947
that everything has improved.

281
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:10,991
Would that be right?

282
00:24:11,074 --> 00:24:13,452
No, ma'am, it's not just an improvement.

283
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:16,371
She's in

284
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:18,206
perfect health.

285
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:20,459
How?

286
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:23,378
Exactly! I've never seen
anything like this before.

287
00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:26,882
Of course, once in a blue moon,
things like this do happen,

288
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:28,758
and there's no telling why.

289
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:31,386
We usually call them miracles.

290
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:34,806
I think, ma'am, that Chae-ni

291
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:37,225
has been blessed with a miracle.

292
00:24:40,187 --> 00:24:41,104
A miracle?

293
00:24:41,730 --> 00:24:43,815
This child is a miracle child.

294
00:25:31,071 --> 00:25:35,033
CHOI YEONG-JUN

295
00:25:46,086 --> 00:25:49,005
This is Choi Yeong-jun.
Please leave a message.

296
00:25:49,506 --> 00:25:51,258
Hello, Director Choi. It's me.

297
00:25:52,133 --> 00:25:53,927
King Jeon-bok of Myeong-dong.

298
00:25:54,469 --> 00:25:56,263
Call me when you get this.

299
00:26:06,106 --> 00:26:09,109
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

300
00:26:09,192 --> 00:26:11,403
APOCALYPSE ON DECEMBER 31ST

301
00:26:11,486 --> 00:26:14,948
RECEIVE SALVATION
AND BE GRANTED ETERNAL LIFE

302
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:25,458
APOCALYPSE
SALVATION

303
00:26:33,466 --> 00:26:35,051
What do we do now, Mr. Son?

304
00:26:35,552 --> 00:26:38,179
How will we ever face Ms. Kim now?

305
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,806
You tell me.

306
00:26:40,307 --> 00:26:43,643
I refused, but you two insisted on
roping me into this. So tell me.

307
00:26:44,352 --> 00:26:45,437
Mr. Son.

308
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:49,274
If you hadn't assumed Chae-ni was dead,
we wouldn't be in this mess.

309
00:26:49,941 --> 00:26:50,775
Assumed?

310
00:26:51,401 --> 00:26:52,235
Listen.

311
00:26:52,861 --> 00:26:54,654
She was definitely dead.

312
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:56,281
She didn't have a pulse.

313
00:26:56,364 --> 00:26:59,075
How could a dead person come back to life?

314
00:26:59,159 --> 00:27:02,287
You went as far as to dispose of
a perfectly healthy person in the hills.

315
00:27:02,370 --> 00:27:04,623
Quiet. Temporarily laid to rest,
not disposed of.

316
00:27:05,707 --> 00:27:07,292
Besides, did I act alone?

317
00:27:07,375 --> 00:27:08,835
You're even worse than I am.

318
00:27:08,918 --> 00:27:12,339
How could you, her friend,
dump her body in a garbage pit?

319
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:16,926
Mr. Son!

320
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:20,096
That's why I said we shouldn't do it.

321
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:23,475
Of course, there it is!
There go the waterworks again.

322
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:27,812
You look like a thug,
but you cry and sulk at the drop of a hat!

323
00:27:27,896 --> 00:27:30,732
Do you know how ghastly
your crying face is?

324
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:34,736
Don't make fun of people's looks.
You shouldn't do that.

325
00:27:34,819 --> 00:27:37,322
Do you think I'm making fun of your looks?

326
00:27:37,405 --> 00:27:38,657
I'm not.

327
00:27:39,574 --> 00:27:41,409
Wait, you weren't? Really?

328
00:27:41,493 --> 00:27:43,328
Of course not.

329
00:27:43,411 --> 00:27:47,040
I was going for a double whammy
by making fun of your looks and sulkiness.

330
00:27:47,123 --> 00:27:48,500
Get a clue, Sappy Sap.

331
00:27:48,583 --> 00:27:50,794
With your runny nose.
God, you drive me nuts.

332
00:28:15,276 --> 00:28:17,362
I told you not to drink from the bottle.

333
00:28:22,784 --> 00:28:23,743
By the way,

334
00:28:24,244 --> 00:28:26,830
any news about the illegal dumping
in the hills?

335
00:28:26,913 --> 00:28:27,747
What?

336
00:28:28,248 --> 00:28:29,332
Right, that.

337
00:28:29,416 --> 00:28:32,252
I actually went earlier
and gave them a good talking-to.

338
00:28:32,335 --> 00:28:34,003
Any time now. Don't worry.

339
00:28:35,088 --> 00:28:36,047
And your mother?

340
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:38,091
What?

341
00:28:38,174 --> 00:28:40,009
Did you make it clear to her

342
00:28:40,093 --> 00:28:43,346
that we're not sending her to Hawaii
but the Hawaii Resort in Bugok?

343
00:28:45,432 --> 00:28:48,977
Yeah, that. Well, you know…

344
00:28:49,978 --> 00:28:52,564
She knows our situation, after all.

345
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:55,316
She didn't seem too disappointed.

346
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:16,588
What are you even doing?

347
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:19,048
I just have some things to think about.

348
00:29:19,132 --> 00:29:20,467
Do you have to do it there?

349
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:22,802
Yeah, I have to do it here.

350
00:29:23,928 --> 00:29:25,180
Well, I'm going to bed.

351
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:27,015
Okay, good night, Ms. Moon Mi-hui.

352
00:29:45,325 --> 00:29:49,287
Here comes my daughter, Cheong,
just as I was opening the fridge door.

353
00:29:51,664 --> 00:29:53,124
Want some ice to cool down?

354
00:29:57,837 --> 00:29:58,671
So that's a no?

355
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:05,762
Are you the problem or am I?

356
00:30:05,845 --> 00:30:09,557
If you are, I can call for a repair,
but who do I call if I'm the problem?

357
00:30:27,659 --> 00:30:29,118
How can this…

358
00:30:32,747 --> 00:30:33,623
How…

359
00:31:29,929 --> 00:31:31,639
Who exactly were your accomplices?

360
00:31:37,812 --> 00:31:38,855
I acted alone.

361
00:31:38,938 --> 00:31:40,857
Ro-bin and Sonie from the flower shop.

362
00:31:40,940 --> 00:31:42,901
I know those two idiots were involved.

363
00:31:43,651 --> 00:31:44,903
Was there anyone else?

364
00:31:45,612 --> 00:31:48,489
I told you. The three of us acted alone.

365
00:31:50,617 --> 00:31:52,368
Do you not know what "alone" means?

366
00:31:53,870 --> 00:31:56,497
I sure do. I know very well.

367
00:31:58,458 --> 00:32:00,543
The soup's getting cold. Eat.

368
00:32:03,630 --> 00:32:07,258
How did you even plan to travel
without a passport?

369
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:18,186
What did the doctor say?

370
00:32:19,270 --> 00:32:22,482
Did he give you some bad news?

371
00:32:23,691 --> 00:32:25,234
While you were growing up,

372
00:32:25,818 --> 00:32:27,904
there wasn't a day that I didn't pray

373
00:32:29,113 --> 00:32:31,199
nor a single day I had peace of mind.

374
00:32:31,866 --> 00:32:35,328
If I couldn't reach you for just a moment,
my heart would sink.

375
00:32:35,411 --> 00:32:38,665
Every time I took you to the hospital,
my blood ran cold.

376
00:32:40,667 --> 00:32:42,335
That's how scared I've been

377
00:32:43,252 --> 00:32:44,253
for the past 20 years.

378
00:32:47,632 --> 00:32:48,758
But

379
00:32:50,301 --> 00:32:52,261
no matter how scared I was…

380
00:32:54,222 --> 00:32:55,640
I doubt I was as scared as you.

381
00:33:04,273 --> 00:33:05,400
I'm sorry, Grandma.

382
00:33:06,859 --> 00:33:08,486
What are you sorry for?

383
00:33:08,569 --> 00:33:11,698
You've made me
the happiest I've been in 27 years.

384
00:33:13,574 --> 00:33:16,035
The test results were excellent.

385
00:33:16,703 --> 00:33:18,621
He said everything's normal.

386
00:33:19,288 --> 00:33:21,290
I never thought I'd see this day.

387
00:33:21,374 --> 00:33:23,376
You're as clean as a whistle.

388
00:33:23,459 --> 00:33:26,462
The size, shape, and condition
of your heart are all perfect.

389
00:33:26,546 --> 00:33:27,922
Why, that doctor

390
00:33:28,423 --> 00:33:31,467
made a huge fuss, calling it a miracle.

391
00:33:34,512 --> 00:33:35,763
So,

392
00:33:36,723 --> 00:33:37,724
from now on,

393
00:33:38,808 --> 00:33:41,102
live your life to the fullest, okay?

394
00:33:42,145 --> 00:33:45,106
But don't let your guard down
and get regular checkups.

395
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:46,190
What was it, again?

396
00:33:46,691 --> 00:33:50,069
Go see the northern lights or whatever
and that huge-headed rock.

397
00:33:50,737 --> 00:33:53,906
And what was it?
Go see the Iguana Falls or whatever.

398
00:33:53,990 --> 00:33:55,533
And go explore Africa.

399
00:33:56,409 --> 00:33:57,618
You should do it all.

400
00:33:59,287 --> 00:34:00,329
So,

401
00:34:00,413 --> 00:34:01,831
from now on,

402
00:34:02,707 --> 00:34:04,417
live life to the fullest, okay?

403
00:34:05,877 --> 00:34:07,378
Make the darn most of it,

404
00:34:09,005 --> 00:34:10,423
and pay for your own trips.

405
00:34:19,557 --> 00:34:22,560
How will I ever earn enough
peeling onions?

406
00:34:38,117 --> 00:34:38,993
Grandma!

407
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:43,289
Before that…

408
00:34:46,459 --> 00:34:47,293
REWARD GRAPES

409
00:34:47,376 --> 00:34:48,628
…you need to fill this up.

410
00:34:49,879 --> 00:34:50,838
Until then,

411
00:34:51,339 --> 00:34:54,383
be good, stay healthy, and speak politely.

412
00:34:54,467 --> 00:34:57,720
And don't spit on other people's houses.
Then I'll give these to you.

413
00:34:59,472 --> 00:35:03,309
Come on, Grandma. I'm not seven.

414
00:35:03,392 --> 00:35:05,144
I'm 27 years old.

415
00:35:05,228 --> 00:35:07,188
If you don't like it, best get peeling.

416
00:35:07,271 --> 00:35:08,606
Oh no.

417
00:35:12,193 --> 00:35:13,236
All right.

418
00:35:14,862 --> 00:35:16,906
First, eat all your food.

419
00:35:35,091 --> 00:35:38,594
Yes, this is Kim Jeon-bok of Hearty House.

420
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:49,272
It's been a while, Director Choi.

421
00:36:08,875 --> 00:36:10,168
"Great job."

422
00:36:18,593 --> 00:36:20,553
No more purple lips.

423
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:24,015
No more dull skin.

424
00:36:26,017 --> 00:36:27,476
No more tinnitus.

425
00:36:29,061 --> 00:36:30,104
And no more bruises.

426
00:36:33,691 --> 00:36:35,610
Even my heart's beating fine.

427
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:40,907
There's been a definite improvement
since my near-death experience.

428
00:36:42,533 --> 00:36:44,368
So why do I keep seeing things?

429
00:36:44,452 --> 00:36:47,246
What ye doin'? Get outta there already!

430
00:36:48,915 --> 00:36:50,082
But that place

431
00:36:51,083 --> 00:36:52,668
wasn't even a tunnel.

432
00:37:00,384 --> 00:37:01,677
Could it be time…

433
00:37:02,178 --> 00:37:04,513
I can't even bring myself
to say "time travel."

434
00:37:10,770 --> 00:37:11,938
That's right.

435
00:37:12,438 --> 00:37:15,775
My brain must have been
deprived of oxygen for a long time.

436
00:37:16,275 --> 00:37:18,069
That's for certain.

437
00:37:24,533 --> 00:37:26,619
There's no doubt they were hallucinations.

438
00:37:27,119 --> 00:37:28,037
Wait a minute.

439
00:37:28,621 --> 00:37:30,873
Then in exchange for a working heart…

440
00:37:31,707 --> 00:37:34,210
7 times 5 is 35, 7 times 6 is 42,
7 times 7 is 49…

441
00:37:34,293 --> 00:37:37,129
- 7 times 8 is…
- Don't touch your eyes, idiot!

442
00:37:41,050 --> 00:37:44,428
Did I lose my brain
in exchange for a working heart?

443
00:37:46,639 --> 00:37:49,016
- This can't be.
- Chae-ni, you have a guest outside.

444
00:37:49,100 --> 00:37:50,309
It's a guy.

445
00:37:50,393 --> 00:37:52,061
He's a looker.

446
00:37:53,062 --> 00:37:54,730
Don't touch your eyes. It stings.

447
00:37:55,648 --> 00:37:56,482
Don't move.

448
00:38:00,987 --> 00:38:02,113
Why are you here?

449
00:38:02,613 --> 00:38:03,948
What do you want from me?

450
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:05,783
Here to pay up?

451
00:38:08,035 --> 00:38:09,245
How many times have you died?

452
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:15,209
Me?

453
00:38:15,293 --> 00:38:17,003
Was that the first time?

454
00:38:17,712 --> 00:38:19,046
Or have you died before?

455
00:38:22,216 --> 00:38:24,468
Is he saying he wants to die?

456
00:38:24,552 --> 00:38:26,554
No. That's him.

457
00:38:26,637 --> 00:38:28,556
The guy who reported us
for dumping a body.

458
00:38:28,639 --> 00:38:30,975
When you had
that near-death experience yesterday.

459
00:38:31,058 --> 00:38:32,727
I see.

460
00:38:33,227 --> 00:38:36,981
First, you wreck my suitcase,
then you make a big fuss over nothing?

461
00:38:37,064 --> 00:38:40,568
I reported it for your sake.
So they could at least find your body.

462
00:38:40,651 --> 00:38:42,111
My body?

463
00:38:42,194 --> 00:38:44,280
I'm standing right here, alive and well!

464
00:38:44,363 --> 00:38:46,490
- You were definitely dead.
- No, I wasn't!

465
00:38:46,574 --> 00:38:49,327
You're making me sound like
some kind of freak.

466
00:38:49,952 --> 00:38:50,828
So what happened?

467
00:38:54,790 --> 00:38:55,833
It's a secret.

468
00:38:58,336 --> 00:39:00,254
She's definitely hiding something.

469
00:39:00,838 --> 00:39:02,131
So you can't tell me?

470
00:39:03,758 --> 00:39:05,676
It's a secret because I can't tell you.

471
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:08,179
It wouldn't be a secret
if I could tell you, would it?

472
00:39:15,102 --> 00:39:16,228
Then, have you ever…

473
00:39:24,028 --> 00:39:25,196
heard of Wunderkinder?

474
00:39:26,989 --> 00:39:28,115
What's this

475
00:39:28,657 --> 00:39:31,369
Boon… the King Duck?

476
00:39:31,869 --> 00:39:33,037
I don't even like duck.

477
00:39:33,913 --> 00:39:35,623
Is it a new duck joint or something?

478
00:39:35,706 --> 00:39:39,752
Why do you keep bothering us?
We told you that nothing happened.

479
00:39:39,835 --> 00:39:41,545
See? Nothing happened.

480
00:39:45,466 --> 00:39:46,634
Well, okay, then.

481
00:39:47,176 --> 00:39:48,344
If you say so.

482
00:39:58,396 --> 00:40:00,981
What was that?
We've got ourselves a nutjob, right?

483
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:03,359
What if he finds out about the kidnapping?

484
00:40:03,442 --> 00:40:04,819
It was my idea anyway.

485
00:40:05,736 --> 00:40:09,407
But Mr. Son said we could be in trouble
if the police find out!

486
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:11,283
They'd have no evidence anyway.

487
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:16,831
You grabbed my suitcase
and camcorder, didn't you?

488
00:40:17,706 --> 00:40:20,501
No. They're probably still
in the abandoned greenhouse.

489
00:40:21,877 --> 00:40:23,295
You didn't delete the footage?

490
00:40:24,046 --> 00:40:25,297
No.

491
00:40:25,381 --> 00:40:27,508
You died,
and we were so freaked out that--

492
00:40:28,801 --> 00:40:30,428
Oh, for God's sake!

493
00:40:30,511 --> 00:40:32,888
You're peeling my share
of the onions for today.

494
00:40:32,972 --> 00:40:35,891
And tomorrow and the day after that
and after that! All yours!

495
00:40:44,733 --> 00:40:47,194
Mr. Son? It's Ro-bin.

496
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:49,572
Okay, goober. Talk later.

497
00:40:53,576 --> 00:40:56,203
I knew I shouldn't have gotten mixed up
with those bozos.

498
00:40:57,538 --> 00:40:59,373
Everything's going sideways.

499
00:41:03,419 --> 00:41:06,672
Please, Rala.
Why are you giving me a hard time too?

500
00:41:11,260 --> 00:41:12,720
That's it, you beauty.

501
00:41:34,950 --> 00:41:38,829
Okay, your turn for lunch.
Today's menu is jjajangbap. Go eat.

502
00:41:38,913 --> 00:41:41,499
Un-jeong, you should also…
You're already gone.

503
00:41:41,582 --> 00:41:45,294
He went alone again, that brat.

504
00:41:45,377 --> 00:41:46,504
Oh boy.

505
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:55,846
There's only one way to find out for sure
if she possesses

506
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:57,890
the ability to resurrect.

507
00:41:59,225 --> 00:42:01,185
Make her need to revive herself.

508
00:42:46,897 --> 00:42:47,773
Extra crispy.

509
00:43:27,730 --> 00:43:29,148
But what if

510
00:43:29,815 --> 00:43:30,649
I'm wrong?

511
00:43:53,756 --> 00:43:54,673
Excuse me.

512
00:44:09,396 --> 00:44:14,652
HAEWON FLOWERS

513
00:44:35,673 --> 00:44:38,425
Is it broken or something?
Why isn't it working?

514
00:44:39,051 --> 00:44:42,179
It'll be worth more if it's working.

515
00:44:43,931 --> 00:44:44,848
What the…

516
00:44:48,185 --> 00:44:50,479
Chae-ni. Chae-ni?

517
00:44:50,562 --> 00:44:51,730
What's wrong with her?

518
00:44:53,899 --> 00:44:54,983
Delete that.

519
00:44:55,067 --> 00:44:56,485
- What's this?
- What? Why?

520
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:03,867
What is it?

521
00:45:04,451 --> 00:45:06,203
What's wrong with Chae-ni?

522
00:45:06,787 --> 00:45:09,081
And what's wrong with you?

523
00:45:10,124 --> 00:45:11,083
Chae-ni

524
00:45:12,459 --> 00:45:13,585
is dead.

525
00:45:17,589 --> 00:45:18,549
Chae-ni

526
00:45:19,591 --> 00:45:21,218
is dead.

527
00:45:27,015 --> 00:45:28,392
I'll buy this from you.

528
00:45:31,311 --> 00:45:33,856
Where the heck did they leave them?

529
00:45:35,065 --> 00:45:37,860
Did they really leave them here?

530
00:45:42,114 --> 00:45:43,365
This is it?

531
00:45:44,116 --> 00:45:46,618
Where's the other stuff?

532
00:45:58,422 --> 00:45:59,339
Damn it.

533
00:45:59,423 --> 00:46:03,135
That bumbling idiot.
How could he leave that stuff there?

534
00:46:47,596 --> 00:46:49,556
What's going on? What's happening?

535
00:47:05,364 --> 00:47:07,032
Where are you right now?

536
00:47:07,741 --> 00:47:08,575
What?

537
00:47:08,659 --> 00:47:11,328
Where else would I be?
I'm making a delivery, of course.

538
00:47:13,664 --> 00:47:16,834
Well, if the flowers
you're supposed to deliver are right here,

539
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:18,794
what exactly are you delivering?

540
00:47:18,877 --> 00:47:19,711
What?

541
00:47:20,212 --> 00:47:21,046
What the…

542
00:47:21,129 --> 00:47:23,340
What do you mean, what?
I should be asking you!

543
00:47:23,423 --> 00:47:25,467
What exactly are you doing?

544
00:47:25,968 --> 00:47:27,636
- What…
- What?

545
00:47:27,719 --> 00:47:29,096
- What…
- What?!

546
00:47:29,179 --> 00:47:30,848
Honey, I gotta go.

547
00:47:34,226 --> 00:47:35,519
Did he just

548
00:47:36,228 --> 00:47:37,229
hang up on me?

549
00:48:00,294 --> 00:48:01,795
What's happening?

550
00:48:01,879 --> 00:48:03,672
I need to get out! Let me out!

551
00:48:07,634 --> 00:48:08,468
What is this?

552
00:48:14,558 --> 00:48:15,642
No way, right?

553
00:48:15,726 --> 00:48:17,352
Lady Trainwreck isn't…

554
00:48:17,853 --> 00:48:20,772
She isn't in there right now, is she?

555
00:49:27,130 --> 00:49:29,925
- That fool still dares to lie!
- Could we get more bracken?

556
00:49:30,008 --> 00:49:31,843
- Coming right up.
- You there!

557
00:49:32,594 --> 00:49:34,721
Twist the legs of the traitor who…

558
00:49:34,805 --> 00:49:36,890
- You scared me!
- That table wants more bracken.

559
00:49:36,974 --> 00:49:40,102
Can't you take it to them?
It's the final scene.

560
00:49:40,185 --> 00:49:42,062
Yes, just a moment.

561
00:49:43,981 --> 00:49:46,316
- Hey, they slipped up!
- Where?

562
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:47,609
You missed it.

563
00:49:49,528 --> 00:49:52,781
Go on and behead me!

564
00:49:55,325 --> 00:49:58,245
LOCATION PROVIDED BY KOREAN FOLK VILLAGE

565
00:49:58,328 --> 00:50:00,038
- Hey, look right there!
- Where?

566
00:50:00,122 --> 00:50:01,832
Oh, I see it!

567
00:50:01,915 --> 00:50:05,085
I heard they shoot scenes live nowadays.
Looks like it's true.

568
00:50:05,168 --> 00:50:09,214
A hospital gown in the Joseon Dynasty?
Why, that's something.

569
00:50:09,297 --> 00:50:11,008
I bet someone's in big trouble.

570
00:50:11,758 --> 00:50:13,343
I'm the one who caught it.

571
00:50:22,352 --> 00:50:23,687
Oh, right.

572
00:50:29,359 --> 00:50:30,193
Hello.

573
00:50:30,902 --> 00:50:31,778
Honey.

574
00:50:33,071 --> 00:50:34,948
Yes, sure. I'm heading back right now.

575
00:50:35,907 --> 00:50:39,036
No, I had some business
to quickly attend to at City Hall.

576
00:50:40,203 --> 00:50:41,455
No, right now, I'm…

577
00:50:41,955 --> 00:50:43,457
I'm already on my way back.

578
00:50:43,957 --> 00:50:44,791
What?

579
00:50:45,375 --> 00:50:47,753
No, I swear. I'll be back soon.

580
00:50:48,295 --> 00:50:49,546
Why's this happening again?

581
00:50:49,629 --> 00:50:52,841
Stop trying to change the subject.
When will you be back?

582
00:50:52,924 --> 00:50:53,759
What?

583
00:50:54,426 --> 00:50:55,886
I…

584
00:50:56,720 --> 00:50:57,846
An hour?

585
00:51:00,265 --> 00:51:01,308
The thing is,

586
00:51:01,892 --> 00:51:04,644
I'm going as fast as I can,
but there's traffic--

587
00:51:09,316 --> 00:51:11,276
Fine, I was playing hooky. So what?

588
00:51:12,444 --> 00:51:14,571
You think all I have to do
is make deliveries?

589
00:51:15,072 --> 00:51:17,032
I have personal business too.

590
00:51:17,115 --> 00:51:18,158
Okay?

591
00:51:18,742 --> 00:51:21,912
The person I hate most in the world
might be in danger.

592
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:24,998
So hang up, and don't wait for me.

593
00:51:25,082 --> 00:51:26,124
I'm busy!

594
00:51:54,778 --> 00:51:55,612
What is that?

595
00:52:43,952 --> 00:52:45,287
Number 3972.

596
00:52:47,122 --> 00:52:48,874
So you're looking for something too.

597
00:53:12,647 --> 00:53:14,608
Her power isn't resurrection?

598
00:53:15,984 --> 00:53:17,027
Could it be…

599
00:53:19,487 --> 00:53:21,740
Wow, this is insane.

600
00:53:22,824 --> 00:53:24,701
Now she's in international waters?

601
00:53:25,785 --> 00:53:27,621
It was teleportation?

602
00:53:33,752 --> 00:53:34,628
When did you board?

603
00:53:36,087 --> 00:53:37,631
Are you a police officer?

604
00:53:40,467 --> 00:53:43,386
What did that bitch see
to have such a dumb look on her face?

605
00:53:43,470 --> 00:53:45,180
Stop yapping.

606
00:53:45,263 --> 00:53:48,308
Let's not waste time
and just throw her overboard as fish food!

607
00:53:49,059 --> 00:53:49,893
Okay.

608
00:53:58,235 --> 00:54:00,362
Help me.

609
00:54:28,932 --> 00:54:31,268
Has Madam King arrived already?

610
00:54:56,626 --> 00:54:58,920
Long time no see, Director Choi.

611
00:55:05,427 --> 00:55:07,429
LIFETIME ACHIEVEMENT AWARD
CHOI YEONG-JUN

612
00:58:50,193 --> 00:58:55,198
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi
